  "texts": [
    "For this reason, the YOLOv7 algorithm was chosen to be used in the study.",
    "The original YOLOv7 architecture consists of four modules: input, backbone, neck and head.",
    "The input module resizes the input image to a standardized pixel size (640 × 640) to fulfill the input size specifications of the backbone module.",
    "The backbone of the original architecture consists of convolutional blocks, batch normalization process, and SiLU activation function (CBS), extended efficient long-range attention network (E-ELAN) and Max-Pool-1 (MP1) modules.",
    "The task of the backbone part is to extract feature maps from the input image."
  ],
